description.narrative: Annual planning, monitoring, and reporting processes were streamlined resulting in harmonized documents and results-oriented processes across the office. Applying global COVID-19 instructions, guidance, and tools for programme planning, monitoring, and reporting allowed the office to implement and monitor programmes during the year and manage risks for staff and partners. Capacities of staff and partners were strengthened in the use of Rights and Results-Based Management, the adjusted Harmonised Approach to Cash Tranfer Standard Operating Procedure;and in the use of e-tool applications. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:23/12/2021
